        "id": 2382931,
        "name": "Dan Kravitz",
        "username": "Dan_Kravitz",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/958977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-03-23T00:54:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Near the top of my list of underrated Burgundy vineyards.</p>\n<p>Bright dark ruby color.  Aromas are powerful, with red cherries, red raspberries, slight secondary sous-bois and intense minerality.  The palate is teenage vigorous, much more like a five year than fifteen plus year Pinot.  The texture is muscular, but not lacking in weight and solidity.  The flavors have good intensity, the balance is excellent, the wine has the ripeness and acidity that are hallmarks of this vintage.  Rated 92.5, up to 3 points of improvement likely over the next 10 years.</p>\n<p>This was opened pop-and-pour, I had a glass with lamb chops, the rest of the bottle went in the fridge to explore tomorrow, when I expect it to soften without losing any intensity.  A wonderful bottle, hope to post on the rest tomorrow.</p>\n<p>Dan Kravitz</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
