        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/958977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-03-23T23:09:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Have not had a Rapet Corton for quite a while.  In general, I find this a very reliable producer.  But I remember a previous bottle of the 2002 Pernand \u2018Vergelesses\u2019 was older than this one.  Also I had three bottles of their '02 Corton Charlie, one premox the other two glorious (IIRC, all drunk over a few years at about 10 years of age).  From pre-board times, I remember buying them for a retailer I worked for and always being pleased.  However I would imagine any red Corton from them would need a lot of time.</p>\n<p>Dan Kravitz</p>",
